An Act relative to multi-family zoning in MBTA communities.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 3A of chapter 40A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
2 Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following subsection:-
3 (d) In the event that an MBTA community has reached the threshold required for it to be
4 consistent with local needs whereby low or moderate income housing exists in the MBTA
5 community in excess of 10 per cent of the housing units reported in the latest federal decennial
6 census of the city or town, as defined in section 20 of chapter 40B, such MBTA community shall
7 not be subject to this section.
